00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:48.899
And second, we know that no one can prevent what Jehovah foresees from coming true.

00:00:48.899 --> 00:00:53.859
All of Jehovah's prophecies come true.

00:00:53.859 --> 00:00:58.539
Now to illustrate the first point that Jehovah can see into the future, let's consider

00:00:58.539 --> 00:01:06.819
two remarkable prophecies concerning the destruction of Jerusalem and its temple.

00:01:06.819 --> 00:01:12.099
Now we know that through the Prophet Jeremiah, Jehovah foretold that Jerusalem and the temple

00:01:12.099 --> 00:01:14.939
would be destroyed by the Babylonians.

00:01:14.939 --> 00:01:16.819
Did it come true?

00:01:16.819 --> 00:01:17.819
Absolutely.

00:01:17.819 --> 00:01:20.500
In 607 BCE.

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:22.379
But Jehovah went further.

00:01:22.379 --> 00:01:26.819
He said that Jerusalem would be rebuilt.

00:01:26.819 --> 00:01:29.620
They will rebuild the ancient ruins.

00:01:29.620 --> 00:01:35.739
They will raise up the desolated places of the past, and they will restore the devastated

00:01:35.739 --> 00:01:37.620
cities.

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:41.219
